retty quick. It\'s about to get really cold there.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1120813'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-01 17:45:00','3rd attempt in 3 days. May one be fatal soon? Push to dig in before the snows will be now. Expect a shuffle on the board and possibility of death increased to substantial. Fingers 4-7 and around Chepuzi camp. Indians on ALL of LAC currently on full alert status. \nhttps://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/india-china-tension-chumar-transgress-indian-side-lac-pangong-tso-india-china-border-tension-646518\nhttps://www.latestly.com/india/news/indian-army-foils-chinese-transgression-bid-in-chumar-day-after-thwarting-another-attempt-to-alter-lac-status-quo-reports-2001200.html','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1121086'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-01 18:06:00','First tweets of shots fired? https://mobile.twitter.com/rakshasaKalnemi/status/1300840528498446337\nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/TheZaiduLeaks/status/1300801812799393793\nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/drapr007/status/1300773693094653952','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1121106'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-01 18:37:00','https://mobile.twitter.com/JudeDwain/status/1300849190176722945\nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/prashant_92/status/1300844083582136320','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1121131'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-01 21:12:00','Tweet of coffin/Funeral 1 hr ago\nPaying Tribute to Officer Coy Ldr Nyima Tenzin, Vikas Regiment,SFF, Indian Army,martyred on Aug 30, defending #India against intruding Chinese PLA troops at Pangong Tso. offered 33 yrs of service to protect India as a #Tibetan who remain grateful for hosting His Holiness. \nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/sonamrigzin1/status/1300869067872509952\nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/sonamrigzin1/status/1300869067872509952/photo/2\nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/sonamrigzin1/status/1300869067872509952/photo/1','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1121247'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-01 21:26:00','Posted 7 min ago\nhttps://youtu.be/2cWcnbDyHo8\nPublished on Sep 1, 2020\nA Tibetan soldier in the Special Frontier Force’s Vikas battalion has martyred and another Tibetan man from the same unit sustained injuries, possibly from the same incident at the LAC. The two have been identified as deceased Company Leader (Coy Ldr) Nyima Tenzin, 51, and Tenzin Lodhen, 24, (rank not available). Sources say that the Company Leader died after he stepped on a landmine while others say that he died of a gun shot wound to his neck. While there are two narratives of how the Tibetan soldier died, his death is confirmed as his body was handed over to his family in Sonamling Tibetan settlement on Tuesday by the army, covered with the Indian and Tibetan flag. He is survived by his wife and three children. His remains will be cremated at 6 am on September 7, 2020.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1121276'),(3,'Balzac','2020-08-28 18:24:00','Here\'s a good piece regarding China\'s preparations to fight a two front war: \n\"Second, the violence in Ladakh has also allowed Beijing to examine the degree of coordination that exists within the Indo-US strategic partnership. As Indian and Chinese soldiers clashed with medieval-style weapons in the Galwan Valley,  Beijing paid close attention to how the United States reacted.\"  https://www.9dashline.com/article/india-china-rivalry-towards-a-two-front-war-in-the-himalayas','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1118294'),(3,'username-deleted 93584','2020-08-24 20:52:00','Thanks for sharing the link!','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1115330'),(3,'jumpupanddown','2020-08-20 13:58:00','Thanks to @msanc for highlighting the above.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1111808'),(3,'Grogu','2020-08-12 04:25:00','https://amp.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3096981/china-india-border-talks-stall-sparking-calls-modi-get-tough\nhttps://www.newsweek.com/china-debuts-new-weapons-near-border-india-says-its-ready-long-period-tensions-1524454','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1105081'),(3,'Ruminandum','2020-08-09 18:31:00','Posturing is necessary, neither side can afford to \'lose face.\' That said, neither side can afford to \"shoot first,\" either. \nAn impasse/stalemate is good, in this instance.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1102880'),(3,'Grogu','2020-07-31 02:23:00','https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/694779-india-to-deploy-35-000-more-troops-along-lac-with-china','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1094376'),(3,'Grogu','2020-07-31 02:23:00','https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/694779-india-to-deploy-35-000-more-troops-along-lac-with-china','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1094378'),(3,'Grogu','2020-07-22 16:11:00','Interesting aside.... https://www.reuters.com/article/us-taiwan-china-defence/chinese-military-threat-on-the-rise-taiwan-foreign-minister-warns-idUSKCN24N0M5\nChinese analysts must be going nuts lately. What would you do were you China? Open multiple fronts? Flex? Or back it (the plan) up for the first times in 40+ years?','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1085634'),(3,'fisherdbus','2020-07-22 21:13:00','The US presently has decided to confront China rather than either cooperate in endeavors or let China be number one World leader. China wants to be the indispensable nation. Leadership also  fears Democracy among its citizens. Projecting power around the World helps it with its goals. Generally it has gone right up to the edge of a military conflict but with recent conflict with India seems to be testing the limits by aggression rather than just assertiveness. Note: Hong Kong. In incremental ways...building and defending islands, etc there are likely to be skirmishes. They can use that to keep population looking outward.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1085982'),(3,'fisherdbus','2020-07-22 21:40:00','You might find this interesting. China expansionist. https://twitter.com/sehof/status/1285776470665654272?s=21','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1085998'),(3,'Grogu','2020-07-22 21:51:00','Thanks!','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1086005'),(3,'Grogu','2020-07-22 21:52:00','Check this out @fisherdbus https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/07/22/china-houston-texas-consulate/5484966002/','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1086006'),(3,'cdob63','2020-07-17 16:04:00','@MCowley, I would feel a whole lot better about the odds of avoiding violence if I didn\'t know that The Leader Of The Free World was threatening to help.   However, staying low on this one because on past form nobody in the gummint will actually do anything.   Thanks for the warning, though.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1082124'),(3,'MCowley','2020-07-18 09:19:00','@cdob63, He may inadvertently help - he\'s extremely capable of bringing attention to things, but who know what would happen if he tries to intervene.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1082760'),(3,'MCowley','2020-07-19 15:10:00','I live in hope that his bluster will help on this one. He\'s second to none as a hype man and I think the more attention this gets, the less likely there is to be conflict','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1083482'),(3,'JChr','2020-07-11 09:11:00','You are a class act. Some very thoughtful insights.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1077001'),(3,'Orao','2020-07-07 18:06:00','The regional military command is now getting directives from senior officials.  Where the blame for the first battle could be pinned to lower level Chinese/Indian “pawns”, any follow up battle will be known by both sides as a senior intelligence directive.  These orders would undermine any bilateral diplomacy remaining, and when weighing the gains for each side against losses, a long term strategy makes far more sense to both sides, in my opinion. @ManuPV','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1073939'),(3,'eshriver','2020-07-07 18:24:00','Thanks Orao, good info!  Where did you find it?  I\'m new to this, so just building a library of sources.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1073961'),(3,'Orao','2020-07-07 18:40:00','its a semi-educated guess based on all the articles I’ve read.  I have to fill knowledge gaps and I believe China utilizes lower level military as scapegoats when attempting to mend and maintain Indian ties','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1073970'),(3,'jumpupanddown','2020-07-02 19:30:00','Generally agree with this take.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1070640'),(3,'Orao','2020-06-28 22:53:00','the DS-DBO road','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1068095'),(3,'KitsonJ','2020-06-24 09:28:00','These are wildly different capabilities though! The units involved were not mechanised and certainly not amphibious.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1064560'),(3,'mrmoo','2020-06-24 11:52:00','Different units  yes- but it\'s about organisational ability, adaptability, and instructional follow thru\nIt\'s as close as they can get without a valid provocation','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1064643'),(3,'leadzeppelin','2020-06-23 15:13:00','Hi, I\'m new here. This is the first question I want to forecast. If China says later on that there had taken fatalities too later on, would that count for \'Yes\' to this question? I supposed the question asked if there would be a fatality due to further violence?','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063903'),(3,'K-M-G','2020-06-23 15:33:00','Hi. As for the casualties mentioned in my link I believe they occured prior to \"between 19 June 2020 and 30 September 2020\" timeframe of the question. They have to occur in the timeframe of the question to resolve it as \"yes\".\nGood luck with forecasting. Don\'t take too many questions at once. That was my beginner mistake.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063932'),(3,'Grogu','2020-06-20 23:38:00','Unfortunately, my gut is telling me the PRC is going to get aggressive on multiple fronts. This next two weeks is critical in how I will forecast in other theaters. Thanks for the nod.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062011'),(3,'cafebedouin','2020-06-20 23:41:00','Probably not a bad approach.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062014'),(3,'ManuPV','2020-07-04 10:57:00','I find this question fascinating, because though the base probability should be fairly low, there are a series of factors that multiply it.\nApparently there has been construction going on after the clash, by the Chinese side probably. Do you think this implies that the clash might be retaken soon? @A356','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1071752'),(3,'A356','2020-07-06 15:36:00','I still think there is a possibility of another clash, but as you mentioned in your update today, tensions seem to be much lower.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1073155'),(3,'ManuPV','2020-07-06 19:08:00','Yes, I agree. But for knowing it for sure we should try to figure out first why the Chinese have decided to abandon their camp and how the Indians convinced them to do so.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1073311'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-01 23:42:00','It\'s hitting all the news over the last hour. Prevailing news being reported is \"shot in the neck\".\nCompany Leader Nyima Tenzin, 51, was reportedly killed by a gunshot in the neck. He is said to be from the Tibetan settlement in Choglamsar near Ladakh’s capital Leh, and had 33 years of service. The injured man is Tenzin Loden, 24, also from Choglamsar settlement. The incident took place on Saturday night.\nhttps://www.tibetsun.com/news/2020/09/01/chinese-bullets-kill-tibetan-soldier-injure-one-in-border-clash','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1121338'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-05 17:44:00','The First Moutain Strike Group just got to the LaC with ultra-light howitzers that can be placed by helicopter near/at all those observation points the Indians just took.\nBuildup is getting out of hand... ALL ALONG THE LaC... not just Ladakh.... the more troops... the hotter it is getting in that chilly environment.\nhttps://zeenews.india.com/hindi/india/in-4-weeks-china-can-take-any-action-indian-armys-first-mountain-strike-reached-ladakh/742125/amp?__twitter_impression=true\nYesterday China urged India \"refrain from deliberately hyping and disseminating negative information.\" Basically... \"don\'t tell anybody how easy it was to take those positions from us last week, capture an army post and take POW\'s... we\'ll give you back your porters in exchange for our troops. Sorry about your Special Forces commander\". Lmbo\nhttps://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-india-china-idUKKBN25W0CM','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1124586'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-05 18:51:00','ITBP Indo-Tibetan Border Police (militia and law enforcement) took many new positions last night. As the actions like this continue, so do the chances of a casualty increase.\nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/VisitorA8Planet/status/1302294305374052352\nhttps://www.opindia.com/2020/09/itbp-india-china-control-key-points-lac-chief-focus-contruction/amp/?__twitter_impression=true\nIt took two days to find out about the Special Forces officer. We may find out more about last nights actions over the next few hours.\nI doubt China will sit idle while India builds a road through where China was sitting 10 days ago....\nOne thing is sure...China is relentless in keeping what it considers its own....','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1124607'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-05 19:08:00','This tweet and a recently posted on Times of India (then quickly taken down) ITBP map seem to indicate that India may currently control the border well into China... for the moment.\nhttps://mobile.twitter.com/adgpi/status/1302137608697335808','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1124622'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-10 18:41:00','Talks in Russia just ended... how the next 24 hours progresses will be affected by the statements released in the next few minutes.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1129260'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-11 15:25:00','26-year-old soldier martyred on \nIndia-China border \nSachin Verma, Shimla Atar Rana, a brave son of Kupvi Tehsil of Chaupal subdivision of Shimla district of \nHimachal Pradesh, serving the motherland in lndian Army, has been martyred while serving the country. It is being reported that Shaheed Atar Rana was serving in Punjab Regiment and was posted on the Line of Exclusive Control (LAC) in the Indo-China border in \nArunachal Pradesh. Although the cause of death has not been officially confirmed yet, the brave son has made his supreme sacrifice while serving the country.\n2hrs ago... https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=en0E06Wl-MQ\n@ddorsey','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1129855'),(3,'Grogu','2020-09-12 15:38:00','Here is video of the beginning of latest skirmish.. https://twitter.com/i/status/1304788292219666433\nReleased 15min ago.\nClubs and spears again... yesterday eve. Southern shore of lake. Up to 40 dead from reports coming in.\nI try to keep you all updated... alas... only a few aren\'t anchored...or tied to sunk costs.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1130649');
