t to do so through other means can be sued by the IOC for billions.  Second is a pride issue.  It would be an international embarrassing to Japan if they are not able to pull off the summer Olympics as China pulls off the winter Olympics early next year.  Of course, Japan and China being long time historical rivals.  It sounds like there is no chance that the games will be cancelled or postpoined.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1281198','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(124,1,'probahilliby','2021-05-24 05:46:00',0,'Mass vaccinations going on, the non-nengotiable attitude of the event organizers, the declining COVID cases, and the following article convinces me almost with certainty. Less than 1%.|https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/tokyo-olympics-to-open-even-if-covid-19-cases-rise-in-japan','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1281123','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(125,1,'Scappleby','2021-05-23 23:44:00',3,'Japan has approved both Moderna and Astra-Zenica last 3 days. They\'re pushing hard to keep this going and it seems like we\'re past the point of no-return. Although they currently only expect seniors to be fully vaccinated by end of July roughly 15% of prefectures say they won\'t make that timeline. I expect it will look very different, and possibly very lacklustre, but it seems almost certain to go ahead.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1281079','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(126,1,'Jimbo_C','2021-05-22 17:08:00',5,'Recent Sky News report says it is going.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1280702','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(127,1,'oracle100','2021-05-22 00:23:00',20,'big fine for Japan is they don\'t hold it and according to Olympic committee it is going ahead. on the not holding it side, most Japanese people don\'t seem to want to hold it.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1280474','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(128,1,'rpmiller4','2021-05-21 23:24:00',2,'Lowering my forecast. Athletes are vaccinating ahead of the games, and they were eligible to travel to Tokyo as early as March. [https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Tokyo-2020-Olympics/Japan-to-let-Olympic-athletes-in-as-early-as-March]. IOC refuses to cancel the Olympics even in a state of emergency [https://www.espn.com/olympics/story/_/id/31482937/ioc-vp-says-tokyo-olympics-take-place-even-state-emergency-place-covid-19]. Even if cases go up. [https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/tokyo-olympics-to-open-even-if-covid-19-cases-rise-in-japan] Currently, the rate of new daily cases is dropping.|As one member of the Japan Olympic Committee noted, \"We’re starting to reach a point where we can’t even cancel anymore\". (See PBS Newshour link).|My take is it\'s going to get increasingly more difficult to cancel due to sunk costs and momentum, and especially the increasing costs of reversing the decision.|Macron is expected to attend [https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/french-president-macron-attend-tokyo-olympics-minister-2021-05-21/].|Once a considerable portion of athletes starts to settle in, it\'ll become even harder to cancel.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1280445','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(129,1,'Blooobird','2021-05-21 16:48:00',10,'This is the last chance! Having already been postponed a year there is no opportunity to delay the games any longer. Japan wants it to happen. The IOC want it to happen. It will probably happen.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1280244','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(130,1,'Bdouglas','2021-05-21 16:04:00',25,'IOC VP statement at news conference to AP (Only IOC can cancel) that even if it’s under a state of emergency in Tokyo or other parts of Japan it will go ahead.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1280232','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(131,1,'lerenard','2021-05-21 13:42:00',18,'https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/fretting-about-covid-most-japan-firms-say-olympics-should-be-cancelled-or-2021-05-20/','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1280160','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(132,1,'HoldMyBeer','2021-05-21 05:58:00',20,'Japanese organisers/government seem pretty unwavering at 