7B (1). Can you imagine the political fallout for wasting this money when there is a literal nuclear disaster cleanup still happening in your country?|2. Geopolitical bragging rights - Either Japan holds the first games after the Covid-19 outbreak, or China does. That\'s up to the Japanese government and Olympic organisers.|3. Further reduction on the realization/discovery that Tokyo City could be on the hook to the IOC for lost earnings, suggestion is this is up to $1.5B (1).|1. https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/olympics-cancel-the-tokyo-games-huge-consequences-and-a-financial-quagmire','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279785','Upvote\n    (2)',NULL),(137,1,'PensAreFun','2021-05-20 14:11:00',25,'Increasing COVID-19 Incidence will force delay or cancellation.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279712','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(138,1,'noetel','2021-05-20 12:44:00',13,'The games seem unpopular in Japan and the risk of it causing a significant spike in Japanese cases seems high, but the Japanese leaders seem to be sticking with the plan and there would be a strong status quo bias to keep it going. https://www.economist.com/asia/2021/05/19/the-tokyo-olympics-are-safe-and-secure-insist-japanese-politicians','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279665','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(141,1,'saltyPistachio','2021-05-20 11:22:00',91,'With further dropping covid-cases and Japan being an island, it is plausible the organizers will present admissible hygiene and safety protocols.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279639','Upvote\n    (0)',0),(142,1,'NattyB','2021-05-20 05:04:00',20,'Athletes will all be vaccinated.  Case numbers are falling.  Huge pressure to “get back to normal.”','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279513','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(143,1,'Ravi-Ivaturi1574726980','2021-05-20 00:59:00',5,'While it\'s conceivable that Covid-19 could play spoilsport, the decision to cancel is a political choice. At a time, when Covid-19 is on the retreat in most of the developed nations and the fact that these games have already been postponed previously, makes either cancellation or postponement highly unlikely.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279463','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(144,1,'CynicFan','2021-05-19 20:32:00',0,'While Japan is severely lagging in vaccinations, the games will go on.  The Olympic committee makes most of its money from television so even if Japan limits spectators, the games will go on.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279407','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(145,1,'Skyreichel','2021-05-19 18:20:00',15,'The initial likelihood was low, but the clear message from the Japanese people is not something to dismiss. We\'re basically looking at the economics and desire for the world to portray COVID as a fading thing VS. Japanese cultural cohesiveness and doing what is best for the greater good.|I think the government will bow to the international pressure over the homegrown, but there is no guarantee.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279367','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(146,1,'Yassenoff','2021-05-19 10:49:00',61,'At some point the relatively young Japanese government may begin to fear the prospect of electoral defeats unless the Olympics are cancelled.  However, it is also likely the games will be postponed to 2022.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279172','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(147,1,'Bdouglas','2021-05-19 07:53:00',42,'Japan times article quote “there would be little surprise if she cancelled it” re Yuriko. 3 day virtual meeting, 80% want to postpone or cancel, Japan doctors protest, pandemic at second peak in country','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279152','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(148,1,'Terry-Smith','2021-05-19 04:45:00',7,'Raising my odds due to the doctors group news release. But again, if the Olympics are going to be cancelled, why are other sports still going on? Here is sumo wrestling from a few days ago, in Tokyo! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eNCz7i4J70U  Sumo has been both with spectators and without spectators this year. It\'s not like the Japanese don\'t know how to do sports safely.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279104','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(149,1,'I-salute-you','2021-05-19 03:56:00',30,'Only 5 olympics ever been cancelled - and all because of war.  1920 olympics was not cancelled, even with Spanish flu pandemic.  Only IoC can cancel the games, not strictly the hosts (although they could withdraw).  Result would be a huge insurance payout.  But 80% of population opposed to games.  Based on past, it won\'t be cancelled but we are still in a pandemic','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1279087','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(150,1,'Rickburger','2021-05-18 17:19:00',93,'With Japan\'s doctors leading the call for cancellation, this must be taken seriously.  Link https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2021/05/18/coronavirus-covid-live-updates-us/','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1278817','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(151,1,'Bobbiekar52','2021-05-18 13:13:00',50,'With calls from doctors to cancel, hospitals are at max, increasing chance to cancel. \nOnly 3% vaccinated means it is unlikely to improve soon.  So even though organizers feel that they can safely hold the Olympics, a massive increase in population being infected and/or hospitalized could prevent the ability to host.  Picture the situation in India ...','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1278687','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(152,1,'SE_Meyer','2021-05-18 06:06:00',0,'Tokyo governor Yuriko Koike could ultimately be crucial for letting the Games happen under her responsibility. Despite mounting pressure from public opinion amid scarcity of vaccines, at the beginning of the 100 day-countdown to the Paralympics start she reportedly said:\n\"We\'ll make preparations to realize safe and secure games so that the event will be a light of hope\"\nhttps://jen.jiji.com/jc/i?g=eco&k=2021051600412','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1278604','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(153,1,'jalduenda','2021-05-18 01:54:00',0,'Olympics will happen with all precautionary measures we know.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1278533','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(154,1,'Burkedale133','2021-05-17 22:19:00',69,'New outbreak makes it look unlikely, but there has been a lot of investment in holding it, and maybe they think they can manage the athletes -most of whom are probably vaccinated.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1278474','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(156,1,'keith-huggins','2021-05-17 10:50:00',10,'It would appear there is significant pressure for the Games to be cancelled. Another postponement is not an option by the IOC.\nThere is also significant pressure from  stakeholders for the games to proceed.\nAccording to a poll conducted in March 2021, 59% of respondents were in not in favour of holding the Games in the midst of a pandemic, 30% supporting the event. The polls seem to vary dependent on the reporting  but showing a trend to postpone/cancel.\nToshihiro Nikai,  the Secretary General of the ruling Liberal Democratic Party suggested that the Games could be cancelled dependent on control of the pandemic, but this was quickly backtracked by him with the Prime Minister, Yoshihide Suga signalling a no- change attitude in the Government indicating perhaps a level of discussion being held as to a cancellation.\nThe British Medical Association have advised against holding the Games, given Japan’s poor record in controlling the virus.\nPressure may be relieved (at a significant loss of income) in that there will no spectators. Foreigners will almost certainly will prohibited from entering the country.\nThe participants in the Games will be subject to a regime of testing and social distancing by their home organisations and the IOC. The World Athletes President, Sebastian Coe believes the Games will proceed given the testing regimes he experienced at a half marathon test event in Sapporo this month.\nFrom the Stakeholders point of view, the official Japanese budget of $15 Billion has climbed to $26 Billion and rising. This would be written down as a loss if the games if the Games were cancelled. The IOC who are the owners of the Games are determined for the Games to proceed to protect the 73% of their income by way of broadcasting rights.\nIt is reported that Japanese companies have paid some $3 billion in sponsorship deals with International broadcasters spending significant amounts (NBC paying $1.4 billion for rights).\nThe Games are the exclusive property of the IOC and only they can terminate the contract between them and the host city of Tokyo. The IOC does have an obligation to the health of the athletes and could cancel if this was threatened (a case could be made here due to the pandemic). Should Tokyo unilaterally pull out, the organising committee would be responsible for all risks and losses.\nThere is also a symbolic significance as the Games would show a revival of Japan post Fukushima and Tsunami according to  Professor Jack Anderson at the University of Melbourne.|Given the IOC’s refusal to even consider a cancellation and the corporate finances spent, the chances of the Games proceeding are positive in that a degree of the expenditure may be recouped.|https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/may/05/sebastian-coe-expects-tokyo-olympics-go-ahead-after-test-event-japan-half-marathon-sapporo|https://www.dw.com/en/could-japan-cancel-tokyo-olympics-over-coronavirus/a-57223286|https://apnews.com/article/tokyo-coronavirus-pandemic-2020-tokyo-olympics-japan-olympic-games-da4ecb601dee77b963005b89631c2724|https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/may/05/sebastian-coe-expects-tokyo-olympics-go-ahead-after-test-event-japan-half-marathon-sapporo|https://www.dw.com/en/olympics-senior-government-figure-admits-tokyo-games-could-be-scrapped/a-57208063 \nhttps://www.ksat.com/sports/2021/04/30/are-the-tokyo-olympics-in-danger-of-being-canceled/ \nhttps://www.bmj.com/content/373/bmj.n962 \nhttps://www.scmp.com/sport/other-sport/article/3133377/why-tokyo-thinks-2020-olympics-show-must-go-even-covid-19-booms \nhttp