full freedom to deal with on-ground situation.\nIndia has something to prove, ‘blood raised’ on both sides. Any ground interactions between patrols could easily escalate to fatal clashes unintentionally.|Negative modifiers (Strategic):\nChina has (largely) achieved its goal, pushing gaining 60 km2 of Indian territory. A period of consolidation to allow tensions to cool would be strategically sensible. \nNumerous Indian government officials said that border tensions will not impact trade between India and China despite some Indian campaigns about boycotting Chinese products. This appears part of a wider intent within the Indian government to prevent further strategic escalation.|Ultimately this is a gut feeling estimate rather than a more quantifiable metric. Given that 15 June was the first fatal clash in 45 years there is no reliable statistical soure to base estimates on the number of annual clashes vs the number that escalate to fatalities.|My estimate leans towards no for all of the reasons above, with the primary reasons being due to China having largely achieved their strategic goals, and India largely being unwilling to escalate to a true inter-state conflict. The residual risk therefore (whilst significant) is due to the potential for local escalation between patrols rather than larger scale strategies on either side. This will accordingly be modified as information comes to light regarding troop numbers and other information between now and September.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1064027','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(714,3,'KatyaWG','2020-06-23 02:28:00',75,'As China seeks to extend its border control as it has in other areas such as Myanmar (other side of China completely), China will see India as an antagonist and push further into India resulting in confrontation.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063636','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(715,3,'juancambeiro','2020-06-23 00:56:00',60,'\" troop buildup is continuing, with villagers in the area and satellite imagery indicating that both sides are still sending in reinforcements. On Saturday, the Indian government released a statement blaming China for trying to erect structures across the disputed border, in territory Delhi considers its own. The government added that it would not allow China to make any unilateral changes to the border ... Though India denies it, independent military analysts have estimated that Chinese troops have seized control of about 23 square miles of Indian territory in the past two months ...  But India’s military ability to retaliate may be limited for now. While its military is one of the world’s largest, it has failed to modernize and stay competitive, watching as China rapidly surpassed it over recent decades. This year, India announced a military budget of nearly $74 billion, compared with Beijing’s $178 billion.\" https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/19/world/asia/india-china-border.html','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063599','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(716,3,'Grogu','2020-06-22 22:56:00',100,'I am glad I am not a part of the analysis team in Bejing  that recommended to Gen. Zhao Zongqi to do this.... they are likely not doing too good today.\nhttps://www.usnews.com/news/world-report/articles/2020-06-22/us-intel-source-china-ordered-attack-on-indian-troops-in-galwan-river-valley','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063471','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(717,3,'Aloha-art','2020-06-22 22:04:00',70,'they do not use guns in the conflict . but they both know kung-fu','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063410','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(718,3,'Censusguyz','2020-06-22 19:14:00',55,'SO, Border Operations being what they are - remote frontier - it begs the question WHat had changed. The answer is Bejing did. THey rotated some shock troops the Border to re build a previously destroyed Chinese Camp. I;m going to GUESS that whoever made the call to send more fresh troops did not accept that the altitude would sap them if they were not acclimated for a while first. These new troops are working along a river that the Chinese are channelizing which does two things, give them a tactical space to work from along side the river instead of in it and it gives them narrow channels they can block and release to surge flood water down stream to the Indian Positions. The China angle is that this is all over a bailey bridge the Indian Army completed the day after the melee.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063273','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(719,3,'fisherdbus','2020-06-22 16:39:00',38,'The Army’s are talking and there is an attempt to diffuse tensions. Modi is denying China has moved into Indian territory. https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/06/india-china-border-standoff-200621111215771.html','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063144','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(720,3,'Irwinfernandes','2020-06-22 15:10:00',90,'The Indian government and its leader will need some face saving after the death of 20 Indian soldiers. Modi has modeled himself as a strongman who can protect the nation. The opposition in India will continue goading him and calling him weak until he acts. China knows it has won this round and can push India further and is likely to try and add to the gains made. It’s a good distraction from their many issues and gives President XI talking points to his base','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1063063','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(721,3,'vaishnavi','2020-06-22 13:10:00',80,'The situation has never been cool, and ongoing instability only increase the possibility of another limited conflict','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062929','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(722,3,'fisherdbus','2020-06-22 05:45:00',62,'https://www.cnn.com/2020/06/17/asia/india-china-military-comparison-hnk-intl-scli/index.html\nhttps://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/3951544','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062783','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(723,3,'Dogopotamus','2020-06-22 03:42:00',52,'Starting out a few percent below the crowd on this one. Both countries seem to be trying to limit further conflict. Outcomes will depend on China not escalating a territorial dispute.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062741','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(724,3,'five-am','2020-06-22 03:17:00',70,'- Changing my stance from previous forecast which was incorrectly placed at 5% probability|- India recently changed its stance on their rules of engagement: \"The Rules of Engagement have been changed and the field commanders have been empowered to order troops to use firearms under extraordinary circumstances, army sources said\". Without top-down control, individual soldiers can act independently which will increase probability of clashes leading to fatalities (https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/defence-news-live-india-china-border-clash-updates-21-june/liveblog/76489161.cms)|------\nPrevious forecast which was pegged at 5% till the recent incident:|\"The only clash between China and India in the past which resulted in fatalities was the Sino-Indian conflict in 1967. After that incident, there were 5 incidents of stand-offs including this current one starting May 2020 (year of incidents: 2013, 2014, 2015, 2017, 2020).|Fights are likely to occur between troops, but are usually restricted to hands, or blunt weapons. It seems highly unlikely that there will be deaths resulting from fists or blunt weapons, although the forecast needs to be adjusted for the unlikely scenario of a lucky strike to the head.|The recent border disputes have started since XJP and Modi came to power (2013 for XJP, 2014 for Modi). Both are seen as nationalists and strongmen who want to build their internal base up while maintaining a strong exterior to the world. This mentality has fueled the disputes over the past 5 years, although stopping short of ordering troops to attack each other with non-blunt weapons to prevent a regional war.|Border disputes started in 2013 when XJP took power and wanted to exert control over China\'s military through a show of force (https://www.theatlantic.com/china/archive/2013/05/are-china-and-india-about-to-fight-over-their-border/275518/). 2014, 2015, 2017 clashes seemed to be about small incursions from construction equipment into disputed territory and usually ahead of Indo-Sino summits.|In 2020, China has ramped up its national security policies. All other nations except for US have not reacted strongly to the new nationalistic push by XJP. If Modi continues to stay on the sidelines, I do not believe that this clash will result in any fatalities as the orders from the top will continue to keep the troops in check.\"','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062726','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(725,3,'Shailendra-Panchal','2020-06-22 00:50:00',55,'The domestic hurdles in the form of public sentiment and political backlash are high enough on both sides at the moment for the leaders of either side not to react forcefully to any real or perceived provocation.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062673','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(726,3,'Syzygy007','2020-06-21 20:01:00',33,'The accidental discharge of weapons at a disputed border could lead to responses later rationalized as \"We thought we were being attacked by terrorist groups\" or the like.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062545','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(727,3,'John-Ryan','2020-06-21 19:58:00',30,'Possible but unlikely. China has enough on their plate without adding this too.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062541','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(728,3,'JamesEE','2020-06-21 19:25:00',47,'Having just had a major incident, with 20 deaths on the Indian side and an unknown number for China, I\'m going to bet that cooler heads will now prevail for a while.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062508','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(729,3,'Ryan-Beck','2020-06-21 14:42:00',55,'Seems like more skirmishes may be likely but I don\'t expect either side to escalate it much beyond that.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062319','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(730,3,'ManuPV','2020-06-21 14:18:00',95,'First estimation, taking into account that the current skirmish might not be over yet.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062293','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(731,3,'Indiresha-Ramachandra','2020-06-21 04:13:00',90,'There is a high likelihood that a single fatality can occur in the next 3 months, before winter sets in. Since  Indian troops have been given greater freedom to respond, the actions of a single person can trigger a fatality.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062138','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(732,3,'osbad4','2020-06-21 02:57:00',20,'A few main angles to my forecast on this subject.\n1. 45 years of history that this is uncommon. Prior beliefs should say risk of confrontation is really low, with the current flare up raising concerns.\n2. China currently seems to have its attentions turned to both containing any domestic issues as well as taking a bigger seat in international affairs as the US has continued to pull back into isolationist approaches.\n3. There appear to be obvious risks that tensions could remain high at the remote and isolated border which keeps this percentage higher. Also there are a good few news reports saying Indian troops have more authority to open fire given provocation.|https://www.wsj.com/articles/india-china-border-clash-shows-rising-risk-in-beijings-territorial-push-11592585381?emailToken=dc5da77a627ab23df99ced6a09ce6cb3R8EO/Or9WNyKBGf+kNM4+I9bi4AfvRs3TR2SHIbJpVuTsDetO0xR4VtGiET4gm5Y9bakMbBEdG01t/AbhgMk9CFrVEbIFCFEd/Cajpe7vX5f4x5o+NFHna1H3feZJFs+U0TF4kaXD31onOGWDalJsA%3D%3D&reflink=article_copyURL_share|https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jun/17/shock-and-anger-in-india-after-worst-attack-on-china-border-in-decades|https://theprint.in/defence/india-changes-rules-of-engagement-at-lac-after-galwan-valley-clash/445392/','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062111','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(733,3,'Grogu','2020-06-21 00:24:00',100,'https://www.google.com/amp/s/www.oneindia.com/amphtml/india/india-china-standoff-live-us-closely-monitoring-border-issue-extends-support-for-peaceful-resolution-3105566.html','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062030','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(735,3,'Jason-Jones','2020-06-20 23:13:00',50,'I think this is a good one to follow. Starting with the crowd. Before looking at the crowd forecast I thought 40% so wasn’t far from the consensus.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1062000','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(736,3,'fisherdbus','2020-06-20 20:43:00',60,'A lot of tensions there. China is rushing tanks and troops to the area. This can be reduced as tensions are reduced.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061929','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(737,3,'Weiwei-Tan-Li','2020-06-20 19:58:00',15,'Virus tensions can increase tensions elsewhere. India is one the hardest hit countries, and China is accused of disinformation. Any kind of nervousness can cause mistakes. I give it a 70% chance that it happens again in a year. So in the next 3 months it should be a bit lower also because an accident *just* happened.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061894','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(738,3,'Grogu','2020-06-20 19:01:00',100,'Indian commanders in Galwan just gave thier soldiers permission to use firearms and the commanders got permission to use any additional means at their disposal... including all those helicopters, fighter jets, rockets, artillery, etc....that just got moved up. \n\"“complete freedom of action” to commanders deployed along the contested Line of Actual Control (LAC) to “handle situations at the tactical level,” two senior officers said on Saturday on condition of anonymity.\"\nhttps://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/no-restrictions-on-firearms-india-gives-soldiers-freedom-along-lac-in-extraordinary-times/story-pCcFAcSAkMRschq50Tom1L.html','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061850','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(739,3,'adrian-zimmermann','2020-06-20 18:06:00',42,'On the \'YES\' side: tensions were growing recently, neither side seemed to back off. On the \'NO\' side: the recent leathal skirmish has attracted a broad international attraction. Will India risk a war on two fronts, against COVID19 and China? Will China run the risk  of losing further international reputation and being seen as bully and bad guy?','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061824','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(740,3,'Marcello-L','2020-06-20 17:22:00',60,'As the tensions between India and China along this border have been steadily growing over recent months, and after India mobilized troops along this border about a month ago ultimately leading to an already lethal confrontation last week, it has become clear that this situation is only escalating. With China showing exhibiting an aversion to “weakness” and an inability to make concessions toward other countries, it has become very clear that China will not let this most recent confrontation with India simply end there.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061819','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(741,3,'username-deleted 90732','2020-06-20 14:04:00',85,'There is almost always a push back, regardless of of who initiated, one or the other will “accidentally” or otherwise, attempt to balance the scales.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061584','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(743,3,'jpalasma','2020-06-20 06:18:00',95,'China is being pretty openly aggressive about this, claiming to have had legal control over the entire area historically.  After a weak Indian response, the Indian people in this area are outraged.  Also, India has invested a lot of infrastructure into the area, and they are not going to want to let China keep seizing more land.  China will ALWAYS keep seizing land along the southern border.  Honestly I would imagine there\'s a lethal confrontation within a week from now.  It appears like both sides are arming and supplying themselves, and just tried to downplay it for a moment to strategize.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061495','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(744,3,'RRG','2020-06-20 05:13:00',35,'The last prediction related to this question left a lot of us eating humble pie. ;-)|So this time, baselining at a (high) 35% - even though the crowd calls this an even shot.|Reasons why I give this a lower probability than the crowd is:\n1) China seems to have achieved their desired result (claim on Gaiwan/embarrass India), and would be happy to sit and watch\n2) India would be wary of escalating the situation (with domestic issues) and would be happy to claim stalemate|The reason why I give this 35% is because of the heightened tensions and the domestic calls of revenge from India. Will watch and revise (downward) in the next 3 months.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061472','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(745,3,'Steve-johnson6','2020-06-20 03:46:00',50,'As shocking as the deaths in June 2020 were, they should be viewed as a preventable training accident and not some organized military action.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061452','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(747,3,'GJTBraun','2020-06-19 19:53:00',45,'Initial forecast. Current crowd forecast at 40%. \nThe two countries have been arguing over the border since they were formed, India (1947) and PRC (1949).\nLine of Actual Control (LAC) has been contested since 1962 war.  Last major conflict was in 2017. \nLatest conflict in the Galwan Valley, was fought hand-to-hand (weapons not carried, by agreement), on very rugged terrain. Most fatalities were from falls down steep slopes. So base rate difficult to determine, but generally less than one incident per year.  \nCurrent tensions are high, and both countries are expanding into the area. India recently built road, China expanding tank forces.\nPrediction window is short, only 90+ days. Area becomes inaccessible during winter.\nI\'ll start at 45%, but adjust down very quickly.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061221','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(748,3,'Bobbiekar52','2020-06-19 19:07:00',95,'Lethal means 1. Last time they even threw rocks.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061180','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(749,3,'Censusguyz','2020-06-19 19:00:00',55,'India is pressing on with construction of camp in the valley and the Chinese engineers are brute forcing a path thru the Himalayas for their Mountain Tank Force.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1061161','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(751,4,'Ryan-Beck','2021-07-20 15:39:00',100,'Sounds like news is reporting it\'s open. https://www.dw.com/en/berlins-controversial-humboldt-forum-opens-its-doors/a-58332615','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1310275','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(752,4,'Columbus','2021-07-20 13:08:00',100,'Open now','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1310206','Upvote\n    (1)',NULL),(753,4,'Columbus','2021-07-20 10:43:00',100,'Opening today \nhttps://www.humboldtforum.org/de/','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1310183','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(754,4,'42','2021-07-07 14:38:00',100,'official opening scheduled with reduced number of laudators for July 20th.\nhttps://www.berliner-kurier.de/berlin/ohne-worte-schloss-wird-eroeffnet-ohne-das-architekt-und-oberster-spendensammler-reden-li.169348','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1304949','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(755,4,'WayZ','2021-07-06 13:23:00',99,'It seems that it\'s planned for the 20th of July so it seems highly likely','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1304290','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(756,4,'flyn','2021-07-03 17:54:00',0,'Most likely not. Too much tech out there to flash this and that. Old school and new school spy junk influencing people to do stupid stuff. The only way to open and guarantee no gamesmanship is to strip ass naked and have mandated showers with NATO approved soap and you better wash that ass real good.','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1303202','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(757,4,'lenn','2021-06-25 21:04:00',98,'https://www.humboldtforum.org/','https://www.gjopen.com/comments/1298489','Upvote\n    (0)',NULL),(758,4,'SE_Meyer','2021-06-24 12:38:00',79,'\"Ticket bookings to visit the exhibitions will start from July 13 on.\"|https://www.regioactive.de/party/endlich-offen-berlin-humboldt-forum-